00:44:48.215 --> 00:44:51.575
But. I... Same thing happened
to me. you know. when I joined
the army; it's a marriage of sorts.

620
00:44:51.735 --> 00:44:55.735
Oh. on prom night.
That's psychotic.

621
00:44:55.895 --> 00:44:58.695
How could you
possibly join the army?

622
00:44:58.855 --> 00:45:02.175
I just... It's something I felt like
I had to do. It's hard to explain.
I mean. I know it doesn't make sense.

623
00:45:02.335 --> 00:45:06.655
No. it doesn't make any sense.
Do you know how much time I spent
on. on this masochistic cycle...

624
00:45:06.815 --> 00:45:09.495
just trying to figure out
what I'd done to drive you away?
- Nothing.

625
00:45:09.655 --> 00:45:12.095
Yeah. well. you tell me that now.
It's a little late.

626
00:45:12.255 --> 00:45:16.655
And I thought you'd been murdered
or brainwashed or... At least.
I'd hoped that's what had happened.

627
00:45:16.815 --> 00:45:18.775
Well. I'm sorry to disappoint you.

628
00:45:18.935 --> 00:45:22.695
So. you know. Come on. spill. What have
you been doing the last ten years?

629
00:45:22.855 --> 00:45:26.655
- Well. you must've had worthwhile
experiences you wanna tell me about.
- Bad experiences.

630
00:45:26.815 --> 00:45:29.255
- You met people?
- Bad people.

631
00:45:29.415 --> 00:45:31.295
- You're pathetic.
You know what you need?
- What?

632
00:45:31.455 --> 00:45:34.375
- Shockabuku.
- You wanna tell me what that means?

633
00:45:34.535 --> 00:45:39.175
It's a swift. spiritual kick to the
head that alters your reality forever.

634
00:45:39.335 --> 00:45:43.775
Ooh. that'd be good.
I think.

635
00:45:43.935 --> 00:45:46.495
So. listen. I was thinking
I could pick you up for the reunion
around 7:00? We go...

636
00:45:46.655 --> 00:45:51.975
Wait a minute. Let me get this straight.
You are asking me to go as your date
to the reunion?

637
00:45:52.135 --> 00:45:55.535
- Yes.
- It's unbelievable.

638
00:45:55.695 --> 00:45:57.535
Well. you know.
what the hell.

639
00:45:57.695 --> 00:45:59.775
- You know. I'm not even
planning on going.
- Really?

640
00:45:59.935 --> 00:46:03.615
Really. I'm... I was just gonna
be mean about them on the radio.

641
00:46:03.775 --> 00:46:06.335
- You know.
- Yeah. yeah.
- Besides. Marty. it's...
it's just gonna be depressing.

642
00:46:06.455 --> 00:46:10.855
Maybe. But listen. if you wanna go.
I can't think of any reason
why we wouldn't go together.

643
00:46:11.015 --> 00:46:14.095
- I can.
- I think if you can open up.
forget. forgive a little.

644
00:46:14.255 --> 00:46:18.935
- And I think it'd be good for you.
and I'll be on time.
- Showing up would be a big step.

645
00:46:21.535 --> 00:46:23.575
- Well. I'll think about it.
- Really?

646
00:46:23.735 --> 00:46:26.375
- Yeah.
- Oh. my God! It's Marvin and Debi.

647
00:46:26.535 --> 00:46:28.575
It's me. Amy.

648
00:46:28.735 --> 00:46:31.655
- Amy!
- Yes! You're still together?

649
00:46:31.815 --> 00:46:36.535
Oh. God. you were
the coolest couple!

650
00:46:36.695 --> 00:46:38.775
- Whoa. whoa.
- Still are. Oh. I'm so sorry.

651
00:46:38.935 --> 00:46:41.815
- Here. you want my drink?
- That's okay. No. no. God.
- No. no. don't worry about a thing.

652
00:46:41.975 --> 00:46:44.735
Debi. I love your show.
It's so timeless.

653
00:46:44.895 --> 00:46:47.935
- Yeah. it does run
a little long sometimes.
- Marvy. are you here for the reunion?

654
00:46:48.095 --> 00:46:50.495
- Sure.
- Where you been these last ten years?

655
00:46:50.655 --> 00:46:53.135
- Yeah. Marv. where ya been?
- You look great.

656
00:46:53.295 --> 00:46:55.135
Thanks. I work
at Kentucky Fried Chicken.

657
00:46:55.295 --> 00:46:58.095
- You do not.
- I do. I sell biscuits and gravy
all over the southland.

658
00:46:58.255 --> 00:47:01.735
- No.
- Mm-hmm.
- You're so funny. He's a funny guy.

659
00:47:01.895 --> 00:47:06.015
- You know. Tim. my husband...
- Listen. why don't I get you two another
drink and you guys can just catch up.

660
00:47:06.175 --> 00:47:09.335
- Oh. could I have a Stoli
with three olives and an onion?
- Yeah.

661
00:47:09.495 --> 00:47:12.735
- Oh. I'll have what she's having.
- Sure.

662
00:47:16.655 --> 00:47:18.495
Oh. hi.

663
00:47:24.535 --> 00:47:27.535
That girl down there.
she doesn't trust me anymore.

664
00:47:27.695 --> 00:47:31.295
I don't know why.
I'm trying to earn back her trust.

665
00:47:39.495 --> 00:47:44.215
I'm gonna go downstairs. finish my
drink. walk her to the car. and I'll be
back at the hotel in about a half-hour.

666
00:47:44.375 --> 00:47:46.495
I'll see you there?

667
00:47:50.415 --> 00:47:55.055
- That's him!
- Yeah. we know. Thank you.
We've been following him around.

668
00:47:55.215 --> 00:47:57.135
Well. what's the problem here?
You guys on an hourly rate?

669
00:47:57.295 --> 00:47:59.855
If we observe the subject
in an illegal act...

670
00:47:59.975 --> 00:48:03.175
only then can we intervene
and terminate.

671
00:48:03.335 --> 00:48:06.495
- Yeah.
- Why don't you just go
and shoot the fucker. huh?

672
00:48:06.655 --> 00:48:11.095
Because we're not assassins. Mr. Grocer.
We work for the American government.

673
00:48:11.255 --> 00:48:14.015
Hey. he's coming back.

674
00:48:20.695 --> 00:48:23.415
Ah. fuck you. guys!

675
00:48:23.575 --> 00:48:26.135
Hey. I don't appreciate
being hosed.

676
00:48:27.215 --> 00:48:30.375
- You're exactly the same.
- So are you.
- I am?

677
00:48:30.535 --> 00:48:32.495
- Mm-hmm.
- How so?
- Just like I remembered you.

678
00:48:32.655 --> 00:48:34.375
Oh. yeah? Troubled?

679
00:48:34.535 --> 00:48:37.855
- I'm troubled? Yeah. Well. I got...
I got a few problems. Don't you?
- Sure.

680
00:48:38.015 --> 00:48:40.575
- Yeah? What'd you do about it?
- Well. I tried everything. you know.

681
00:48:40.735 --> 00:48:43.495
I went to the nutritionist.
the herbalist. the psychiatrist.

682
00:48:43.655 --> 00:48:45.375
Really? That's quite a list.
Any of it work?

683
00:48:45.535 --> 00:48:48.375
Can't tell yet. but you gotta try. You
know what I'm saying? It's your duty.

684
00:48:48.535 --> 00:48:52.895
Ah. yeah. patriot. Sure. sure.
So. tell me more about your problems.

685
00:48:53.055 --> 00:48:57.215
And I'll tell you about mine.
And then we'll solve them tonight.

686
00:48:57.375 --> 00:49:00.415
Not so fast.
You're still in the penalty box.

687
00:49:00.575 --> 00:49:03.975
Oh. right. right. right.

688
00:49:04.135 --> 00:49:06.295
Well. thanks
for coming to see me.

689
00:49:06.455 --> 00:49:08.895
Hmm. So. is there
a Mrs. Mysterio?

690
00:49:09.055 --> 00:49:11.255
- No. but I have a very nice cat.
- Not the same.

691
00:49:11.415 --> 00:49:13.695
Well. you don't know my cat.
It's very demanding.

692
00:49:13.855 --> 00:49:17.335
- It? You don't know
if it's a boy or a girl?
- I respect its privacy.

693
00:49:20.095 --> 00:49:22.135
- You happy?
- Kind of.

694
00:49:22.295 --> 00:49:24.895
- Really?
- Sort of.

695
00:49:25.055 --> 00:49:28.255
- We'll talk soon?
- Okay.

696
00:49:32.495 --> 00:49:34.695
It's a nice ride.
Nobody buys American anymore. huh?

697
00:49:51.615 --> 00:49:55.375
- Hello?
- Marcella. what do you got?
- Hey. that town is hot!

698
00:49:55.535 --> 00:49:58.975
I got the stink from an assistant over
at Rothchild's. We prepped together.

699
00:49:59.135 --> 00:50:03.095
- I downloaded everything.
so just call it up.
- I'm on-line.

700
00:50:05.055 --> 00:50:09.215
We've got Steven Lardner.
a.k.a. Steve.

701
00:50:09.375 --> 00:50:11.655
And Kenneth McCullers.
No pseudonym.

702
00:50:11.815 --> 00:50:14.375
Steve was a redshirt tailback
from Ohio State.

703
00:50:14.535 --> 00:50:18.815
McCullers. All-American wrestler
from Northwestern. M.B.A. from the same.

704
00:50:18.975 --> 00:50:22.575
- What are they doing here?
- Well. they're domestic covert
operatives for the N.S.A...

705
00:50:22.735 --> 00:50:26.055
up there as part of a new
"Get Tough on Terror" campaign.

706
00:50:26.215 --> 00:50:29.015
They're looking for an Oswald;
a patsy to take the fall.

707
00:50:29.175 --> 00:50:33.175
- Grocer fed them you.
- Grocer set me up.
- Surprised?
- No.

708
00:50:33.335 --> 00:50:38.255
Well. they were supposed to catch you
in the act. but I guess they
weren't quick enough. right?

709
00:50:38.415 --> 00:50:40.055
- Who's the ghoul?
- Whoa.

710
00:50:40.215 --> 00:50:44.535
This guy is a badass.
Felix LaPoubelle.

711
00:50:44.695 --> 00:50:47.455
An accomplished amateur
with the Basque Nationalists.

712
00:50:47.615 --> 00:50:50.175
Few odds jobs
with the Algerian Separatists.

713
00:50:50.295 --> 00:50:54.415
Went pro with a stunning debut
aboard an elite Caribbean cruise liner.

714
00:50:54.575 --> 00:50:56.855
Oh. that's where I know him from.
He's an asshole.

715
00:50:57.015 --> 00:51:00.655
Did loan-outs for Likkenbakken.
Enjoys. uh. Native American art...

716
00:51:00.815 --> 00:51:04.135
- ballroom dancing. pornography...
- Yeah. yeah. yeah.
What is he here for?

717
00:51:04.295 --> 00:51:07.615
It's part of that Oregon
snafu with that dog. Budro.

718
00:51:07.775 --> 00:51:11.335
So. you're gonna get out of there.
right? I mean. that's not right. right?
You gotta get out of there. right?

719
00:51:11.495 --> 00:51:14.655
- You're on a flight tonight. right?
- It isn't done.

720
00:51:14.815 --> 00:51:17.895
- This is not good.
- I'll do it tomorrow. It's fine.

721
00:51:18.055 --> 00:51:21.415
- Sir. I'm beginning to worry
about your safety.
- Look. I have to go.

722
00:51:21.575 --> 00:51:24.415
Yeah. we all have to go sometime. sir.
but we can choose when.

723
00:51:24.575 --> 00:51:26.335
No one chooses when.

724
00:52:49.855 --> 00:52:51.615
Ya can't come in.

725
00:52:51.775 --> 00:52:55.655
Well. I was in the neighborhood.
so I just stopped by.

726
00:52:55.815 --> 00:52:58.095
Wanted to say hi.
Can I come in?

727
00:52:58.255 --> 00:53:02.575
Ya can come in.
but only for a second.

728
00:53:13.015 --> 00:53:15.095
Unbelievable.

729
00:53:15.255 --> 00:53:17.095
It's exactly the same.

730
00:53:17.255 --> 00:53:19.975
It's a shrine.
It's only temporary.

731
00:53:20.135 --> 00:53:22.535
My apartment burned down
on Devil's Night.

732
00:53:22.695 --> 00:53:26.695
Really? So you never
gave me an answer.

733
00:53:26.855 --> 00:53:29.735
- I said we'd talk later.
- Well. this is later.

734
00:53:29.895 --> 00:53:33.255
See. I figure if we go together
we have a much better chance
of gettin' out of there alive.

735
00:53:33.415 --> 00:53:37.335
You know. we can partner up.
watch for traps. you know. Go tandem.

736
00:53:37.495 --> 00:53:39.935
I think it'd be a lot safer
than if we lone-wolfed it.

737
00:53:40.095 --> 00:53:45.215
- I have to say I'm curious as to
what ten years has done to you.
- You too.

738
00:53:45.335 --> 00:53:49.535
Is. uh... Is that the same bed?

739
00:53:49.695 --> 00:53:53.495
- Uh-huh.
- The magic bed.

740
00:53:53.655 --> 00:53:56.215
The magic carpet. Wow. Hmm.

741
00:53:58.815 --> 00:54:01.735
I'll tell you what. I'll give you
an answer if you give me an "airplane".

742
00:54:01.895 --> 00:54:04.215
- Okay.
- Cool!

743
00:54:05.655 --> 00:54:07.575
- Ready?
- Okay.

744
00:54:09.055 --> 00:54:13.295
- Keep your feet low there.
- I remember.
- Oh. it's been ten years.

745
00:54:13.455 --> 00:54:15.655
- Oh!
- Fly! Be free.
- I'm flying!
- Be free.

746
00:54:15.815 --> 00:54:17.455
- Emancipation!
- Are you free?

747
00:54:17.615 --> 00:54:20.215
- Of course. Okay.
- What if your Dad comes in?

748
00:54:20.375 --> 00:54:22.775
You can give him one too. Okay.

749
00:54:22.935 --> 00:54:25.695
You can pick me up at 7:00.

750
00:54:25.855 --> 00:54:29.015
Put me down.
You can pick me up.

751
00:54:33.895 --> 00:54:36.175
Okay. you can go now.

752
00:54:36.335 --> 00:54:40.215
You want me to leave right now?
You don't wanna. you know. maybe watch
CNN. Crossfire. something romantic?

753
00:54:40.375 --> 00:54:45.015
- No. "airplane" was quite enough.
- Okay. I'll go. That's fine. I'll go.

754
00:54:45.175 --> 00:54:47.015
But this. this night...
tomorrow night... the reunion...

755
00:54:47.175 --> 00:54:50.255
is gonna be
an im... important step...

756
00:54:50.415 --> 00:54:53.695
in our. you know.
burgeoning relationship.

757
00:54:53.855 --> 00:54:56.015
You're a fucking psycho.

758
00:54:56.175 --> 00:55:00.615
Don't rush to judgment on something
like that until all the facts are in.

759
00:55:00.775 --> 00:55:03.815
- I'll just let myself out.
- Go.

760
00:55:03.975 --> 00:55:09.015
And. um. you can. you know. lock
the door behind me because. you know.
there's a lot of undesirables around.

761
00:55:09.175 --> 00:55:11.495
I'll call you or...
I'll... I'll go.

762
00:55:21.215 --> 00:55:23.855
Oh. shit. there he is.

763
00:55:27.255 --> 00:55:31.375
Man. why don't we just do his job
so we can do our job
and get the fuck out of here?

764
00:55:31.535 --> 00:55:35.775
What do you mean. "do his job"?
What am I. a cold-blooded killer?
I'm not a cold-blooded killer.

765
00:55:35.935 --> 00:55:39.055
- Now. wait a minute.
- No. you wait a minute.

766
00:55:39.215 --> 00:55:42.655
You wanna kill the good guy. but not be
the bad guy. Doesn't work like that.

767
00:55:42.815 --> 00:55:45.935
You gotta wait until
the bad guy kills the good guy.

768
00:55:46.095 --> 00:55:48.255
Then when you kill the bad guy.
you're the good guy.

769
00:55:48.415 --> 00:55:53.975
So... just to clarify...
if we do his job. we're the bad guys.

770
00:55:54.135 --> 00:55:57.935
- And if we do our job.
we're the good guys.
- Yes.

771
00:55:58.095 --> 00:56:00.375
That's great.

772
00:56:02.735 --> 00:56:05.775
Hey. hey.

773
00:56:05.935 --> 00:56:07.895
Hi. Mr. Grocer.

774
00:56:09.655 --> 00:56:12.295
Oh. he's brown-bagging it today.

775
00:56:20.575 --> 00:56:23.215
Oh. my God.

776
00:56:27.975 --> 00:56:31.095
Easy there. chief.

777
00:56:31.255 --> 00:56:33.335
I don't see hollow point wound care
on the menu.

778
00:56:33.495 --> 00:56:36.575
Up. up. up.

779
00:56:36.735 --> 00:56:39.055
What are you in Detroit for?
The Red Wings need a new goon?

780
00:56:39.215 --> 00:56:42.815
Hi. my name is Melanie. Let me
tell you about some of our specials.

781
00:56:42.975 --> 00:56:46.215
Today. there's the Alfalfa On My Mind.
That's our featured omelette.

782
00:56:46.375 --> 00:56:48.615
Or there's Gatsby's
West Egg omelette.

783
00:56:48.775 --> 00:56:52.415
And if you're in the mood
for something different. there's
the I Left My Heart In San Francheezy.

784
00:56:52.575 --> 00:56:56.135
- What'll you have?
- Two poached eggs.
Scrape off the milky white stuff.

785
00:56:56.295 --> 00:56:59.215
Hash browns. well done. English muffin
for the bread and a coffee.

786
00:56:59.375 --> 00:57:01.855
Whole-grain pancakes
and an egg-white omelette. please.

787
00:57:02.015 --> 00:57:04.855
- What would you like in your omelette?
- Nothing in the omelette.
Nothing at all.

788
00:57:05.015 --> 00:57:08.015
- Well. that's not
technically an omelette.
- Well. I don't want to get into
a semantic argument over it.

789
00:57:08.175 --> 00:57:11.695
I just want the protein. all right?

790
00:57:11.855 --> 00:57:15.055
Come on there. ice man.
live a little. Let Chef Raoul put in
a little cilantro for your liver.

791
00:57:15.215 --> 00:57:18.615
- I don't want that.
- A little onions for the blood.

792
00:57:18.775 --> 00:57:22.855
- What are those?
- Nutrients.

793
00:57:23.015 --> 00:57:25.415
Here's the new stuff. kid.
Durazac-15.

794
00:57:25.575 --> 00:57:27.975
Makes Prozac
feel like a decaf latte.

795
00:57:28.135 --> 00:57:31.095
- You want a couple? I got jars.
- I don't do that stuff anymore.

796
00:57:31.255 --> 00:57:33.895
No wonder you got the shakes.
And don't say "do it".

797
00:57:34.055 --> 00:57:37.255
Because I don't "do it". I ingest
it on orders from my neurophysiologist.

798
00:57:37.415 --> 00:57:41.135
It's legal. In five years.
we'll be puttin' it in the water
for the citizens like fluoride.

799
00:57:41.295 --> 00:57:45.135
That's fascinating. Is there anything
else you wanted to talk about?
Because I was gonna have breakfast.

800
00:57:45.295 --> 00:57:48.895
I heard about that
little blowup at the Ultimart.
It was a wicked. rippin' shame.

801
00:57:49.055 --> 00:57:51.735
- One of yours?
One of your fraternal brothers?
- No!

802
00:57:51.895 --> 00:57:54.215
Hey. listen.
I wanna work with you.

803
00:57:54.375 --> 00:57:58.255
That was some indie frog.
Some Basque whacker from the Pyrenees.

804
00:57:58.415 --> 00:58:00.735
You sure Oregon
doesn't ring a bell?

805
00:58:00.895 --> 00:58:04.215
Pacific Northwest.
a couple of months ago?

806
00:58:04.375 --> 00:58:06.935
Something about you doin'
some wonder dog named Cujo?

807
00:58:07.055 --> 00:58:11.575
- Ohh. Budro. Yes. Budro. Jesus Christ.
- He knows the dog.

808
00:58:11.735 --> 00:58:14.615
- Yeah. I was out there trying to
whack these three junk bond fuckos...
- Yeah?

809
00:58:14.775 --> 00:58:17.935
and these idiots were flushing game
with sticks of dynamite.

810
00:58:18.095 --> 00:58:21.495
And the dog that they borrowed.
little Budro. was a retriever. Get it?

811
00:58:21.655 --> 00:58:25.935
Budro was never a target. Budro was
acting on instinct. I would never hurt
an animal. And I'm offended at the acc...

812
00:58:26.095 --> 00:58:29.455
Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.
Chatty Kathy. Clip your string.
l don't need to know.

813
00:58:29.615 --> 00:58:34.415
But just for the record. here's
what I heard. The marks borrowed
your client's prized hunting pup.

814
00:58:34.575 --> 00:58:37.695
So bad luck for Budro
and bad luck for Blank.

815
00:58:37.855 --> 00:58:41.215
Poodle pumper. Hound hitter.
Pooch puncher.

816
00:58:41.375 --> 00:58:43.775
Let's not talk
about Budro. huh?

817
00:58:43.935 --> 00:58:46.335
What about those two guys
in the Caprice Classic outside?

818
00:58:46.495 --> 00:58:49.295
- The word is you turned two
governments on me. you turncoat.
- Me?

819
00:58:49.455 --> 00:58:51.335
- You.
- Go "G"?
- Yes.
- On you?

820
00:58:51.495 --> 00:58:54.215
- Yes.
- Never.

821
00:58:54.375 --> 00:58:56.695
Listen. why don't we get
